content.p:
(3) A petition for winding up may be presented by: (a) the company;
              (b) any creditor or creditors; (c) any contributory or contributories; (d) all or
              any of the parties specified in clauses (a), (b) and (c) together or separately;
              (e) the registrar; or (f) the Commission.

Consent is said to be free when it is not caused by:
              (1) coercion, as defined in section 15; (2) undue influence, as defined in section 16;
              (3) fraud, as defined in section 17; (4) misrepresentation, as defined in section 18;
              or (5) mistake, subject to the provisions of sections 20, 21 and 22.

item.p:
"Special Economic Zone" or "Zone" means a geographically delineated
                  area within the territory of Pakistan which is notified by the federal government
                  as a Special Economic Zone under section 3 of this Act;

"zone enterprise" means any person who holds a valid licence granted
                  under section 14 to undertake manufacturing, processing, assembling, trading,
                  warehousing or the provision of services in a Special Economic Zone;

"One Window Operation" means the single-point facilitation mechanism
                  established under section 7 to provide all regulatory approvals, licences and
                  permits to zone developers and zone enterprises;
